<title>HUNGARY: Globus posts lower H1 profits,higher sales.</title>
<headline>Globus posts lower H1 profits,higher sales.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six-months ending June 30.</p>
<p>(in millions of forints unless stated)</p>
<p>				   Jan-June 1997     Jan-June 1996</p>
<p>    Operating profit		56.2     vs	113.5</p>
<p>    Pre-tax profit		 103.5     vs	111.6</p>
<p>    After-tax profit	     103.5     vs	111.6</p>
<p>    Net sales revenue	  3,010.8     vs    2,367.9</p>
<p>	Net domestic sales     1,959.3     vs    1,664.5</p>
<p>	Net export sales	 1,051.4     vs	703.3</p>
<p>    Other revenue		  299.8     vs	174.8</p>
<p>    Directs costs of sales   2,398.1     vs    1,687.0</p>
<p>    Indirect costs of sales    716.0     vs	642.5</p>
<p>    Other expenditures	   140.3     vs	 99.7</p>
<p>    Net financial income	  17.3 loss vs	 5.1 loss</p>
<p>	Financial revenue	   12.2     vs	 19.4</p>
<p>	Financial expenditure     29.5     vs	 24.5</p>
<p>    Net extraordinary income    64.5 profit vs     3.3 profit</p>
<p>	Extraordinary revenue    129.8     vs	156.6</p>
<p>	Extraordinary expend.     65.3     vs	153.3</p>
<p>NOTE - Globus Konzervipari Rt is a tinned food and fruit juice manufacturer. The figures were calculated in accordance with Hungarian Accounting Standards and are not audited.</p>
